2. METEOROLOGICAL SITUATION AT 0500: IRELAND LIES BETWEEN HIGH PRESSURE
TO THE EAST (L02OHPA) AND LOW PRESSURE TO THE WEST (986HPA) IN A MODERATE
SOUTHEAST FLOW. A WEAK FRONT LIES OFF THE SOUTHWEST COAST WITH ATLANTIC
FRONTS BREAKING THROUGH LATER TODAY IN STRENGTHENING SOUTHEAST WIND.
3. FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM MIZEN HEAD TO SLYNE HEAD TO MALIN HEAD:
WIND: SOUTHEAST FORCE 4 OR 5 INCREASING FORCE 5 TO 6 AND GUSTY THIS MORNING.
FURTHER INCREASING FORCE 6 OR 7 AND GUSTY THIS AFTERNOON.
FORECAST FOR COASTS FROM MALIN HEAD TO HOWTH HEAD TO MIZEN HEAD AND FOR
THE IRISH SEA:
WIND: SOUTHEAST FORCE 3 OR 4. INCREASING FORCE 4 OR 5 THIS AFTERNOON FURTHER
INCREASING 5 TO 6 AND GUSTY LATER.
WEATHER FOR ALL SETT AREAS: FINE IN THE EAST AND SOUTHEAST BECOMING FINE
IN THE NORTH. PATCHY MIST DRIZZLE AND FOG IN THE SOUTHWEST. RAIN IN THE
SOUTH AND WEST THIS EVENING EXTENDING TO REMAINING SEA AREAS LATER.
VISIBILITY FOR ALL SEA AREAS: POOR IN MIST FOG AND PRECIPITATION OTHERWISE
GOOD.
3A. WARNING OF HEAVY SWELL: NIL.
4. OUTLOOK FOR A FURTHER 24 HOURS UNTIL 0600 FRIDAY 22 JANUARY 2016: STRONG
AND GUSTY SOUTHEASTERLY WINDS. OUTBREAKS OF RAIN WITH SOME LOCAL PATCHES
